          <source>This example shows how to use a              <ph id="ph1">&lt;xref:System.Windows.Media.Animation.MatrixAnimationUsingPath&gt;</ph> and a              <ph id="ph2">&lt;xref:System.Windows.Media.MatrixTransform&gt;</ph> to rotate (pivot) an object along a geometric path defined by a              <ph id="ph3">&lt;xref:System.Windows.Media.PathGeometry&gt;</ph> object.</source>
